{
  "__inputs": [
    {
      "name": "DS_PROMETHEUS",
      "type": "datasource",
      "pluginId": "prometheus",
      "pluginName": "Prometheus"
    }
  ],
  "uid": "bcm-process-metrics",
  "title": "BCM Process Metrics \u2014 CPU, Cores, Threads, Contention",
  "tags": [
    "bcm",
    "process",
    "cpu",
    "contention",
    "weka"
  ],
  "timezone": "browser",
  "editable": true,
  "refresh": "15s",
  "time": {
    "from": "now-30m",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "panels": [
    {
      "title": "CPU Contention",
      "type": "stat",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "bcm_cpu_contention_score",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false
        }
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 4,
        "h": 4
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "#EAB839",
                "value": 0.5
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 0.8
              }
            ]
          },
          "decimals": 2,
          "mappings": [
            {
              "type": "range",
              "options": {
                "from": 0,
                "to": 0.49,
                "result": {
                  "text": "NO CONTENTION",
                  "color": "green"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "range",
              "options": {
                "from": 0.5,
                "to": 0.79,
                "result": {
                  "text": "MODERATE",
                  "color": "#EAB839"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "range",
              "options": {
                "from": 0.8,
                "to": 999,
                "result": {
                  "text": "CONTENTION!",
                  "color": "red"
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "value_and_name",
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "orientation": "auto"
      },
      "description": "**How it's calculated:**\n\nContention = `total_CPU_%_all_processes / (num_cores \u00d7 100)`\n\nIn Linux, the CFS (Completely Fair Scheduler) distributes CPU time across all runnable tasks. When the total demanded CPU exceeds available cores, processes compete for time slices \u2014 this is contention.\n\n- **0** = No contention. Total CPU demand fits within available cores.\n- **1** = Full contention. Processes demand 100% of every core.\n\nSource: Derived from `/proc/stat` total CPU and `ps` aggregate CPU.\nIf this reaches **1**, tasks are waiting in the run queue and experiencing scheduling latency \u2014 check `vmstat` column `r` for run queue depth."
    },
    {
      "title": "Total Cores",
      "type": "stat",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "bcm_node_cpu_cores_total",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false
        }
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 4,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 4,
        "h": 4
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              }
            ]
          },
          "decimals": 0
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "auto",
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "orientation": "auto"
      },
      "description": "**How it's calculated:**\n\n`nproc` \u2014 number of logical CPU cores available to the OS.\n\nOn systems with HyperThreading, this is 2\u00d7 physical cores. Each core can independently run one thread at a time through the Linux CFS scheduler. This is the denominator for contention scoring."
    },
    {
      "title": "Weka Core Limit Alert",
      "type": "stat",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "bcm_weka_core_limit_exceeded",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false
        }
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 8,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 4,
        "h": 4
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 1
              }
            ]
          },
          "decimals": 0,
          "mappings": [
            {
              "type": "value",
              "options": {
                "0": {
                  "text": "\u2705 OK (within 17-core limit)",
                  "color": "green"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "value",
              "options": {
                "1": {
                  "text": "\ud83d\udea8 EXCEEDED 17-CORE LIMIT",
                  "color": "red"
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "value_and_name",
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "orientation": "auto"
      },
      "description": "**How it's calculated:**\n\n`1` if total CPU cores consumed by Weka processes > 17, else `0`.\n\nWeka.IO storage processes pin themselves to specific CPU cores using `taskset`/`cpuset`. If Weka exceeds 17 cores, it starves other services (Slurm, NVIDIA drivers) of CPU time.\n\n- **0 = OK** \u2014 Weka within limit\n- **1 = EXCEEDED** \u2014 Weka using too many cores, other services impacted"
    },
    {
      "title": "Weka Core Limit",
      "type": "gauge",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(bcm_service_cpu_cores_total{service=\"weka\"})",
          "legendFormat": "{{hostname}}",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false
        }
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 12,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 4,
        "h": 4
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "#EAB839",
                "value": 14
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 17
              }
            ]
          },
          "decimals": 1
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        }
      },
      "description": "**How it's calculated:**\n\nSum of `CPU% / 100` for all processes matching `weka*`.\n\nExample: 17 Weka I/O threads each at 100% = 17.0 cores used.\nThreshold set at 17 cores (the configured limit)."
    },
    {
      "title": "Active Processes",
      "type": "stat",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "count(bcm_process_cpu_percent > 0)",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false
        }
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 16,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 4,
        "h": 4
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              }
            ]
          },
          "decimals": 0
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "auto",
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "orientation": "auto"
      },
      "description": "**How it's calculated:**\n\nCount of processes with CPU% > 0 from `ps -eo %cpu`.\n\nThis shows processes actively consuming CPU scheduling time. The Linux scheduler only allocates time slices to processes in the `TASK_RUNNING` state. Sleeping/idle processes are excluded."
    },
    {
      "title": "Process Count by Service",
      "type": "stat",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "bcm_service_process_count",
          "legendFormat": "{{service}}",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false
        }
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 20,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 4,
        "h": 4
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              }
            ]
          },
          "decimals": 0
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "auto",
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "orientation": "auto"
      },
      "description": "**How it's calculated:**\n\nCount of all processes (including idle) grouped by service classification.\n\nClassification rules:\n- `weka` = weka*, WekaIO*\n- `slurm` = slurm*, srun\n- `bcm` = cmd, cmsh\n- `mysql` = mysqld\n- `kernel` = kworker/*, rcu_*, cpuhp/*\n- Others = shown by actual process name"
    },
    {
      "title": "\ud83d\udccb Process Details \u2014 CPU%, Cores Used, Threads, Memory",
      "type": "table",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "topk(25, bcm_process_cpu_percent)",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table"
        },
        {
          "expr": "bcm_process_cpu_cores_used",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table"
        },
        {
          "expr": "bcm_process_threads",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table"
        },
        {
          "expr": "bcm_process_rss_bytes",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table"
        },
        {
          "expr": "bcm_process_mem_percent",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table"
        }
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 10
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Value #A"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "displayName",
                "value": "CPU %"
              },
              {
                "id": "unit",
                "value": "percent"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Value #B"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "displayName",
                "value": "Cores Used"
              },
              {
                "id": "decimals",
                "value": 2
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Value #C"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "displayName",
                "value": "Threads"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Value #D"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "displayName",
                "value": "RSS"
              },
              {
                "id": "unit",
                "value": "bytes"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Value #E"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "displayName",
                "value": "Mem %"
              },
              {
                "id": "unit",
                "value": "percent"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "options": {
        "showHeader": true,
        "sortBy": [
          {
            "displayName": "CPU %",
            "desc": true
          }
        ]
      },
      "description": "**How each column is calculated:**\n\n| Column | Source | Meaning |\n|--------|--------|---------|\n| **CPU %** | `ps -eo %cpu` | % of ONE core's time used. 100% = 1 full core. 400% = 4 cores. |\n| **Cores Used** | `CPU% / 100` | How many logical cores this process is using. Derived from CPU%. |\n| **Threads** | `ps -eo nlwp` | Number of kernel-scheduled threads (NLWP = Number of Light Weight Processes). Each thread gets its own time slice from the CFS scheduler. |\n| **RSS (Memory)** | `ps -eo rss` \u00d7 1024 | Resident Set Size \u2014 physical RAM actually mapped to the process. Does NOT include swap or shared pages counted elsewhere. |\n| **Mem %** | `ps -eo %mem` | RSS / total physical RAM \u00d7 100. |\n| **Service** | Pattern match | Classification: weka, slurm, nvidia, bcm, mysql, nfs, system, kernel, or actual process name. |\n\n**Linux scheduling context:** Each thread is scheduled independently by the CFS (Completely Fair Scheduler). A process with 83 threads (like `cmd`) doesn't use 83 cores \u2014 most threads are sleeping. Only threads in `TASK_RUNNING` state consume CPU time. The CPU% shows actual utilization."
    },
    {
      "title": "\ud83d\udd32 Per-Core CPU Usage (each core individually)",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "bcm_cpu_core_usage_percent",
          "legendFormat": "Core {{core}}",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          }
        }
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 14,
        "w": 16,
        "h": 8
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "percent",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "#EAB839",
                "value": 70
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 90
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom",
          "calcs": [
            "min",
            "max",
            "mean",
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        }
      },
      "description": "**How it's calculated:**\n\nTwo snapshots of `/proc/stat` taken 1 second apart:\n```\ncpu0  user nice system idle iowait irq softirq steal\n```\nUsage = `(user\u2082+system\u2082 - user\u2081-system\u2081) / (total\u2082 - total\u2081) \u00d7 100`\n\nEach line in `/proc/stat` is a separate CPU core. Core 0 is the first logical CPU.\n\n**What to look for:**\n- One core at 100% while others idle \u2192 single-threaded bottleneck\n- All cores at 100% \u2192 heavy multi-threaded workload (or contention)\n- Even distribution \u2192 good scheduling, CFS is balancing load\n\n**OS Context:** The Linux kernel tracks CPU ticks per core. Each tick is 1/CONFIG_HZ seconds (typically 1ms). We diff two readings to get the percentage of ticks spent on user+system work vs idle."
    },
    {
      "title": "Per-Core Current",
      "type": "bargauge",
      "datasource": {
